@node M_INTRO "Introduction"

    @{u}Introduction@{uu}

MID-It! is a program that converts music files from format
MMD0/MMD1 to the far more common (standard) MID format 1.
The MMD0/1 format is used by the Amiga music editor MED and
its successors OctaMED and SoundStudio.
In this document I will refer to OctaMED only, with the convention
that, if not otherwise mentioned, all topics apply to MED and
SoundStudio too.

The converter was created due to personal needs: I like to make
music at home with OctaMED and my trusty Amiga, and sometimes I used
to go to a music studio to give a more professional touch to my work.

Well, in short I was very tired of carrying every time my whole
Amiga environment to the recording studios simply because the
sequencer (and the computer, always Atari or Mac) in it was not able
to import MMD modules. :(

So I spent my spare time writing MID-It!.
It allows you to load a (pure MIDI) MMD0 or MMD1 music module and get
it converted in a few seconds to the universal MIDI file format 1!

Once you have the MIDI file, you can edit and use it with most of
the music sequencers existing today, on any computer platform.

Of course I know that OctaMED V6 and SoundStudio are capable of
saving MIDI files too, but can only output format 0 MIDI files
(all data in one big track), while MID-It! happily handles and
saves format 1 (multitrack) files.

The output file is all in all a standard MIDI file format 1, but
its contents can be different, according to the @{" conversion mode " link M_CONVMODE }
and @{" options " link M_CONVOPT } selected.

@endnode


@node M_NEW "What's new"

    @{u}What's new - the latest changes@{uu}

The last released version before this one was 2.6; since then many
changes have been made, and every different kind of improvement
caused the bump of the version number of MID-It; so let's go for
the (interesting?) list of new things :)

Medplayer library is no longer needed at all because the module
loading routines have been integrated (and maybe made even better)
in the main program.

Powerpacker and XPK crunched files are automatically detected
and loaded (as long as you have the needed libraries installed).

Various little changes to the code are included that @{i}should not @{ui}
produce any noticeable effect but help me making the code more
ordered and easier to mantain: this project has been under continuous
developement for two years and some general clean up certainly does
no hurt :)

Several steps have been taken to make the program even more system
and user friendly: the MUI MID-It is now fully localizable (catalogs
will be released as soon as they come ready), and supports those nice
"icon-world" things like appicon, appwindow, tooltypes and so on.
More on this argument in the new @{" Workbench section " link M_WORKBENCH }.
If you want to help me with new language catalogs or workbench icons,
even MagicWB or NewIcons, here's how to contact @{" me " link M_AUTHOR }.

Refer to the @{" history " link M_HISTORY } for more detailed information about the
new things since the last release.


Main changes in V2 over V1
--------------------------

The main new feature in version 2 is a brand new integrated @{" MUI " link M_MUI }
graphic front-end, from which every operation can be performed just
using the mouse - no CLI stuff :)

Anyway, for who does not like MUI (or has a machine that cannot
run it) there is still a CLI version for use from a Shell,
completely compatible with MID-It v1 options interface, that should
work on all Amiga models and every Kickstart from 1.1 to 3.x.

Actually, the conversion engine is exactly the same in both MUI and
CLI version, the (big?) difference is the smart user interface that
makes using it quite a breeze.

Other - less important - improvements are various changes and
enhancements to the conversion routines, so that only the
tracks actually used are output to the result MID file, and the
(currently incomplete) implementation of the new 3x player command,
introduced in SoundStudio 1.0, that allows the definition of a set
of parametrized MIDI messages (control changes, NRPN, etc.) and their
sending.

The routines have been optimized in several other ways and every bug
that has been found in V1 should be completely fixed now.
(As you can see in history, actually it wasn't >:|)

Finally, the last enhancement worth mentioning here is, as you have
surely noticed at this time, this AmigaGuide doc :)

@endnode


@node M_INSTALL "Installing MID-It!"

    @{u}Installing MID-It!@{uu}

Just copy the MID-It! directory wherever you wish.

The files with name ending in _020 are the 68020 optimized
executables, offering just a little more speed; they only work with
68020 or higher processors.

That's all :)

@endnode


