@node M_HISTORY "MID-It! history"

    @{i}@{b}Program history@{ub}@{ui} (last changes first)


   4 Jun 1997 - V2.8b:
   ------------------

    Common changes:
      - No longer medplayer.library dependent thanx to a brand new
        module relocation routine
      - Spanish catalog ready and included


  25 May 1997 - V2.8 (not released):
  ---------------------------------

    Common changes:
      - Fully localized; thanx to a Spanish guy (Mexicano Malo) I
        have met the wonderful ATO crew; a self-made Italian catalog
        is ready and soon the Spanish one should be too

    Changes in MUI version only:
      - Added Workbench features:
        1) When iconified you can drag on it module icons (app-icon)
        2) You can drag module icons into the MID-It (app-)window
        3) MID-It works also as a project icon default tool
        4) Configuration can now be set using tooltypes too
      - The multisong browser has been changed to a more confortable
        slider instead of an integer gadget, and the total number of
        songs contained in the loaded module is shown on the right of
        the slider.


  10 May 1997 - V2.7 (not released):
  ---------------------------------

    Common changes:
      - Added support for XPK and Powerpacked crunched files.
      - Eliminated some redundant code
      - LoadModule() MedPlayer library no longer used; the library
        is needed only for RelocModule() now.

    Changes in CLI version only:
      - Fixed bug: when long path were used, more than 32 chars,
        resulting filenames were messed up.
      - The 'examined files' item at the end report now shows
        the number of all files matching the wildcard specification,
        not only the MMD ones.


  6 May 1997 - V2.6:
  -----------------

    Changes in MUI version only:
      - It is now possible to set a default module path by typing
        it, ended by ':' or '/', in the file string requester, or
        by specifing it using the NAME startup argument.
      - Hopefully solved the problem with read-only text boxes
        changing their size after deiconization.
      - Improved the keyboard cyclechain.

    Changes in CLI version only:
      - Fixed very small bug in the wildcard file scan code.

    Common changes:
      - Added the 68020 optimized executables to the distribution
        archive, the version string and the copyright banner contain
        additional CPU and release infos.
      - Rebuilt everything using SAS C 6.57.
      - Fixed some problems converting tricky hold/retrig slots.
      - The whole converter engine has been revised to be as close to
        the original playroutines as possible.
        Even some bugs should have been replicated to achieve maximum
        conversion fidelity.
      - Fixed bug: the polyphonic aftertouch command (0x0A) sent the
        wrong note number.
      - Fixed bug: when setting a new instrument number without
        playing a note the reference to the instrument of the pending
        note was lost.
        This could cause some note off events to be put on the wrong
        output track.
      - Fixed bug: retrig command on a slot without note generated
        badly formed events on the output file.


  19 Jan 1997 - V2.5b:
  -------------------
      - Fixed Enforcer hits when opening the destination file ASL
        requester after deiconifying the application.
      - Found and corrected a terrible bug that could cause the loss
        of several note events:
        the note delay counter was not reset at the beginning of each
        note slot, so if one slot had a command to set the note delay
        to a value greater than the song current tempo2, not only the
        note was not played (correct behaviour) but the following too
        were skipped, even if they didn't have a note delay command.
      - Little changes to the About information text -
        more 'professional style' now :)
      - The destination filename maximum size is now 255 chars
        (it was 32, and it was a bug).


  8 Dec 1996 - still V2.5:
  -----------------------
      - The hold command (8) now accepts values between 1 and 255
        (was 1-15).


  6 Nov 1996 - v2.5:
  -----------------
      - Added automatic MIDI output optimization.
        This means that some MIDI messages like control changes,
        pitch bends, channel aftertouch and tempo changes are
        monitored during conversion and the ones that just try to set
        an already existing value are simply *not* converted.
        This should help to avoid unnecessary MIDI data send (and
        files are shorter too).


  Jul 1996 - v2.1 and 2.2 (not released):
  --------------------------------------
      - Just playing around with MUI and custom classes...


  3 Jul 1996 - v2.0c:
  -------------------
      - Maybe ready for release though beta testing was made only by
        me :)
      - Reintroduced CLI program for old kickstart users and non MUI
        enthusiasts.


  29 Jun 1996 - v2.0b (very advanced beta stage):
  ----------------------------------------------
      - MUI 3.3 implementation is complete.
      - Optimized MID file output: only tracks holding real data are
        created, whatever conversion mode is used.
      - New argument parsing using ReadArgs.
      - Revised conversion routines, should be a little faster and
        safer.
      - The program now detaches from CLI.
      - Even if the Rexx and Commodities interfaces are not complete,
        it's still possible to iconify and quit the application with
        Exchange.
      - There is still an annoying appearance bug:
        when de-iconizing the application, the read-only text boxes
        can change size.

***************************** V 1 ***********************************

    25 Jun 1996 - v1.9 (not released):
                  Discovered and fixed bug in Channel conversion

    17 Jun 1996 - started workin'on v2.0!

    12 Jun 1996 - v1.8 (not released):
                  Still having troubles when dealing with strange
                  tempo settings; hope I have fixed them now and
                  forever. Some little messagery changes.

    26 May 1996 - v1.7:
                  Corrected bug in retrig commands: the instrument
                  and song transpose were summed to the note value
                  for each retrig.

    18 Feb 1996 - v1.6 (not released?):
                  Corrected bug that caused wrong timing
                  information when secondary tempo was not
                  permanently set at 6.

    19 Nov 1995 - v1.5:
                  Added time shift option and multimodule
                  support.

    17 Sep 1995 - V1.2d (not released):
                  Slight correction: the warn track number for
                  message 'not a MIDI instrument' was wrong.

    13 Jul 1995 - V1.2c:
                  Discovered and fixed bug preventing many
                  MIDI effects from being correctly converted.
                  Lifted max tracks per block to 32 because
                  OctaMED 5+ can save MMD1 modules having
                  blocks made of more than 16 tracks.

    23 May 1995 - No bug reports from beta testers -
                  ready for Aminet upload!

    7 May 1995 - Version 1.2b presents lots of new features:
                 - Wildcard and filename extensions handling
                 - Options -b, -e, -q, -u
                 - A few (minor) bugs fixes
                 - Annotation text saved as text event
                 - Total playing time computed and inserted
                   as text event
                 - Enhanced option parser - can specify
                   multiple options attached, like -qre
                 - Due to wildcard support, inserted scan and
                   conversion statistics

    5 May 1995 - Awful bug discovered and hopefully fixed:
                 various commands from FF1 to FFF caused also
                 a tempo change! -> V1.1b

    30 April 1995 - First release is ready (v1.1a)

    25 April 1995 - Version 1.1 is ready for second phase of
                    beta testing.

       Changes:

       - Corrected bug when inserting program change in smart
         mode - it was put in the track of the previous
         instrument instead of the right one.

       - Added MMD0 comversion
       - Added decimal volumes dealing
       - Added ST and SPD compatibility
       - Added Channel conversion type

    23 April 1995 - Version 1.0 does little, but does it
                    well. Beta testers ask for MMD0 and
                    ST + SPD timing compatibility.

    6 April 1995 - Real (mailed) beta testing begins.

    4 April 1995 - beta version 1.0 is ready.
                   Only BPM, pure MIDI, no instrument data
                   modules.
                   I've already converted thirty modules,
                   only getting polyphony problems with my
                   MIDI keyboard.

    4 March 1995 - project starts

@endnode


